## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **OCR features**: Does `ocr_features.pkl` exist in the project? If not, I'll generate simulated OCR features that produce realistic distributions. If `easyocr` is installed, I'll use it to extract real OCR features. Which approach should I use?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Feature cache**: The existing `features_cache_v2.npz` (94MB) contains pre-extracted features. Should the .py files use this cache or re-extract? I recommend using the cache (with re-extraction as fallback) for speed.

